Former National Football League star, OJ Simpson was arrested by Las Vegas, NE police on 8 charges including kidnapping, armed robbery, assault with a weapon, burglary and conspiracy.
The kidnapping charge carries the possibility of life in prison if convicted.
The robbery was in a Las Vegas hotel and the items stolen were identified as sports memorabilia.
Nevada prosecutors in Clark County, charged Simpson and 5 other men.
Bail was set at $125,000.00 for Simpson.
Charles Cashmore, of the 5, will plead guilty and testify against the others.
